    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nThe foreground color of  `Ignore` with `guifg` set to `bg` isn't changed after changing the `Normal` highlight using `nvim_set_hl()`. When using  `:highlight Normal guibg=...` instead of `nvim_set_hl()` Neovim API, it's changed immediately.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Open Neovim:`nvim --clean`\r\n2. Run: `:set termguicolors | call nvim_set_hl(0, 'Normal', { 'bg': '#2d2d2d' }) | highlight Ignore`\r\n3. Make sure that `xxx` is displayed in white\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe `Ignore` foreground color should be reflected immediately in the new `Normal` background color. This is to say, `xxx` in `:highlight Ignore` shouldn't be invisible because foreground and background colors are the same.\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1261+g09a17f91d\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nN/A\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nmacOS 12.6.7\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\niTerm2 Build 3.5.0beta11\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from master branch",
